                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d761">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/607</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Acting Secretary of
                        State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-23">March 23,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British Ambassador called to see me this evening at my request. The
                    Ambassador again brought up the question of our recognition of the independence
                    of Syria. I replied that I preferred to leave this matter in continued abeyance
                    for the time being. I said that until we knew clearly what our situation with
                    the Vichy Government was, I saw nothing to be gained by raising this new
                    obstacle. The Ambassador said that he understood our position and
                    acquiesced.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >elles</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
